cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.PL, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on optimizing the performance of applications on a specific hardware architecture, the Intel XeonPhi coprocessors. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with parallel applications and optimizing their performance on a many-core platform. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The main goal of the paper is to improve the performance of applications on the XeonPhi coprocessors. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the task granularity and resource partitioning of applications, which are related to programming language constructs and design. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes an automatic approach to optimize the performance of applications, which can be seen as a software engineering problem.
